# ─────────────────────────────────────────────
#  HOW IT WORKS
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────
with st.expander("📖 How the angle detection works", expanded=False):
    st.markdown("""
    **Angle estimation (no extra pose model needed):**

    | Body angle | Bounding-box aspect ratio | Chosen shirt view |
    |---|---|---|
    | −45° (left turn) | narrow (~0.35) | Left-side image |
    | 0°  (facing cam) | wide   (~0.55) | Front image     |
    | +45° (right turn)| narrow (~0.35) | Right-side image|

    The horizontal center of the box relative to the frame width
    breaks the left/right symmetry.

    **Pipeline per frame:**
    1. YOLOv8-seg detects shirt bounding box + coarse mask
    2. SAM refines to a pixel-accurate mask
    3. Morphological ops (close + open) sharpen edges
    4. Angle estimated → correct shirt view selected
    5. Alpha-blend: original pixels outside mask, shirt inside

    For even better accuracy you can plug in a **pose estimator**
    (e.g. MediaPipe Pose) to get the exact shoulder angle.
    """)
